## Selected Publications

> Publications are grouped by year and tagged by type (Journal Article, Workshop Paper, Conference Paper, Report, Policy Brief, Research Brief).

### 2025

- [UNESCO/G20 Report] Squicciarini, M., Jurowetzki, R., & Pfeiffer, C. (2025). Toolkit to Reduce Inequalities Connected to the Use of Artificial Intelligence. UNESCO. https://unesdoc.unesco.org/ark:/48223/pf0000395373
- [Research Brief] Sogaard, A., Rogers, A., Adler-Nissen, R., Belongie, S., Moeslund, T. B., & Jurowetzki, R. (2025). Artificial General Intelligence and its Societal Implications. CAISA. https://caisa.dk/forskning/agi-and-its-societal-implications
- [Policy Brief] Jurowetzki, R., Adler-Nissen, R., & Pedersen, M. A. (2025). A Modular Approach to Digital Sovereignty: From Ambition to Action with a National AI Orchestration Layer. CAISA. https://caisa.dk/forskning
- [Journal Article] Jurowetzki, R., Hain, D. S., Wirtz, K., & Bianchini, S. (2025). The private sector is hoarding AI researchers: what implications for science? AI & Society, 40(5), 4145–4152. https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00146-024-02171-z
- [Journal Article] Elmholdt, K. T., Nielsen, J. A., Florczak, C. K., Jurowetzki, R., & Hain, D. (2025). The hopes and fears of artificial intelligence: a comparative computational discourse analysis. AI & Society, 40(6), 4765–4782. https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00146-025-02214-z
- [Workshop Paper] Larsen, B. & Jurowetzki, R. (2025). Using reasoning for citation context classification. SCOLIA '25, CEUR-WS Vol. 4022, 4–10. https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-4022/paper-01.pdf
- [Conference Paper] Jurowetzki, R., Abbonato, D., & Squicciarini, M. (2025). Mapping AI's Labor Impact: A Task Exposure Framework for Occupational Analysis. Conference paper, 40 pp.

